{
  "texts": [
    "As a result, many pitfalls can be generalized across different problem categories in image processing (image-level classification, semantic segmentation, object detection and instance segmentation), as well as imaging modalities and domains.",
    "A detailed discussion of all pitfalls can be found in Supplementary Note 2.",
    "One of our key objectives was to facilitate information retrieval and provide structure within this vast topic.",
    "Specifically, we wanted to enable researchers to quickly identify which metrics are affected by which types of pitfalls.",
    "To achieve this, we developed a comprehensive taxonomy that categorizes the different pitfalls in a semantic manner."
  ]
}